Manage implementation tasks for a change

Track task progress through status, start, complete, and shelve actions.
Tasks are organized in waves for phased implementation. Use 'ready' to
find actionable tasks across changes.

Examples:
  ito tasks status 005-01_add-auth
  ito tasks next 005-01_add-auth
  ito tasks ready
  ito tasks ready 005-01_add-auth
  ito tasks start 005-01_add-auth 1.1
  ito tasks complete 005-01_add-auth 1.1

Usage: ito tasks [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  init      Create enhanced tasks.md [aliases: in]
  status    Show task progress [aliases: st]
  next      Show the next available task [aliases: nx]
  ready     Show all ready tasks (pending tasks in earliest incomplete wave) [aliases: rd]
  start     Mark a task in-progress [aliases: go]
  complete  Mark a task complete [aliases: co]
  shelve    Shelve a task (reversible) [aliases: sv]
  unshelve  Restore a shelved task to pending [aliases: us]
  add       Add a new task (enhanced only) [aliases: ad]
  show      Print tasks.md [aliases: sh]

Options:
      --json
          Output as JSON

      --no-color
          Disable color output

      --help-all
          Print the full CLI reference (equivalent to `ito help --all`)

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
